> On Nov 21, 2012 8:10 AM, "Todd Whiteman" <toddw@activestate.com
> <mailto:toddw@activestate.com>> wrote:
>
>     Hello,
>
>     The first Komodo IDE 8.0.0 alpha (pre-release) is now available for
>     testing. You can download it here:
>
>         http://downloads.activestate.com/Komodo/releases/8.0.0a1/
>
>     This is the first of many Komodo 8 pre-release builds, which will
>     lead to an official Komodo 8.0.0 final release in 2013. The major
>     changes in Komodo 8 are:
>
>       * *Massive Code Update*
>         Komodo has received a number of updates to it's underlying code
>         base. Komodo now uses Mozilla 17 code base, Python 2.7 and
>         Scintilla 3.2.1, as well as other updated internal components.
>         All of which means:
>           o Better performance - with faster start times as well as
>             using less CPU and memory resources
>           o Better hardware support - by detecting and supporting modern
>             computer systems
>           o A better browser preview - supporting the latest and
>             greatest web technologies
>
>       * *Cocoa 64-bit*
>         On the Mac, Komodo has moved from 32-bit Carbon to 64-bit Cocoa.
>         Komodo will work better when running on the latest Mac OS X
>         computers. With Komodo 8 we've also added initial support for
>         Retina displays, with the Komodo editor component being able to
>         show crystal clear fonts under this mode.
>
>       * *New Languages*
>         The following language changes have been made to Komodo 8:
>           o Laravel Blade language added - a PHP templating language
>           o Sass syntax checking added
>
>     You can view the release notes for a full list of changes in Komodo 8:
>
>     http://docs.activestate.com/komodo/8.0/releases/ide.html#bug_fixes-8.0.0a1
>
>     The Komodo IDE 8.0.0 alpha builds can be trialed by anyone (you
>     don't need to hold a Komodo IDE license). We'll continue releasing
>     additional Komodo 8 alpha and beta builds every 4-6 weeks until the
>     final release sometime in 2013.
>
>     You can contact us about Komodo 7 questions and problems using any
>     of the mediums below:
>
>     forums http://community.activestate.com/products/Komodo
>     email http://listserv.activestate.com/mailman/listinfo/komodo-discuss
>     bugs http://bugs.activestate.com/enter_bug.cgi?product=Komodo
>     irc irc://irc.mozilla.org/#komodo
>
>     Cheers,
>     Todd
>
